==Worldwide distribution==
===Alpine tree lines=== The alpine tree line at a location is dependent on local variables, such as [[aspect (geography)|aspect]] of slope, [[rain shadow]] and proximity to either [[geographical pole]]. In addition, in some tropical or island localities, the lack of biogeographical access to species that have evolved in a [[subalpine zone|subalpine]] environment can result in lower tree lines than one might expect by climate alone.
Averaging over many locations and local [[microclimate]]s, the treeline rises {{convert|75|m|ft|round=5}} when moving 1 degree south from 70 to 50°N, and {{convert|130|m|ft}} per degree from 50 to 30°N. Between 30°N and 20°S, the treeline is roughly constant, between {{convert|3500|and|4000|m|ft}}.<ref name=korner/>
